            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> parsley </strong>and <strong>coriander </strong>(including the stalks!)<strong> </strong>with the <strong>peeled garlic </strong>and<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> ground cumin</strong>,<strong> ground paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 3  tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[5 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>chermoula</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don’t have a food processor, use a pestle & mortar!</p>",
